title: Spider-Man versus Formal Attire
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2J9h7hO

by SeerofHope_KnightofDoom

Peter Parker was a capable, clever young man. Even his acquired arachnid abilities aside, Peter’s aptitude got him in to and out of a lot of trouble. On the off chance he couldn’t figure something out, the modern library of Alexandria known as the Internet – or the maternal wisdom of Aunt May – could usually bail him out.

Except, apparently, when it comes to ties.

summary: Can we take a moment to appreciate Nick’s pitch for Spider-Man 4?
title: Can we take a moment to appreciate Nick’s pitch for Spider-Man 4?
body:
It’s well thought out and the scenes he described fit so well into the Spider-Man comedy style.

Honestly it sounds like a great movie. It also sets up a whole new Spider-Man series with Miles Morales, which I would defiantly watch. It’s also just a great way to end a series, even if they didn’t want to continue the story with Miles.

I just love it so much and I’m not seeing too many posts about it so…here we are.

Honestly it sounds like a great movie. It also sets up a whole new Spider-Man series with Miles Morales, which I would defiantly watch. It’s also just a great way to end a series, even if they didn’t want to continue the story with Miles.

I just love it so much and I’m not seeing too many posts about it so…here we are.
